OL,7,FPeople in their 40s may have to work
OL,8,Funtil they are 69 or even 70 if the
OL,9,FGovernment is to stay within spending
OL,10,Fguidelines.
OL,12,FA review by Baroness Neville-Rolfe
OL,13,Fpublished yesterday recommended
OL,14,Fcapping state spending on pensions at
OL,15,F6 per cent of GDP.
OL,17,FIf implemented this would raise the
OL,18,Fpension age from 68 to 69 between
OL,19,F2046 and 2048. Anyone born after 1979
OL,20,Fwould have a pension age of at least
OL,21,F69 under the review.
